properties.Name: TransunionPublicRecord
properties.Description:
Public record information is maintained on a consumer's file in compliance with the Fair Credit Reporting Act (FCRA).

Public Record information is obtained from county, state and federal courts and includes civil judgments, state tax liens, federal tax liens, and bankruptcies. 

The length of time that each record is maintained on TransUnion's database varies by the type of record.

Columns.Name: DocketNumber
Columns.Description: The docket number associated with the legal proceeding.

Columns.Name: PlaintiffName
Columns.Description: The name of the plaintiff bringing the legal action against the Consumer.

Columns.Name: PlaintiffAttorneyName
Columns.Description: The name of the Plaintiff's attorney.

Columns.Name: PaidCivilJudgmentAmount
Columns.Description: The amount paid in the civil judgment.

Columns.Name: ReportedDate
Columns.Description: The date that the legal proceeding was reported.

Columns.Name: AssetsAmount
Columns.Description: The amount of assets involved in the legal proceeding.

Columns.Name: LiabilitiesAmount
Columns.Description: The amount of liabilities of the Customer.

Columns.Name: DateFiled
Columns.Description: The date that the action was filed.

Columns.Name: LiabilitiesPaidDate
Columns.Description: The date the liabilities were paid by the Consumer.

Columns.Name: TransunionActionTypeId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of a TransUnion Action Type.

Columns.Name: TransunionCourtTypeId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of a TransUnion Court Type.

Columns.Name: TransunionResponsibilityTypeId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of a TransUnion Responsibility Type.
